column2: The once-lush green forest had turned into a desolate wasteland. The scorching heat had parched the earth, and the absence of rain had caused the rivers to dry up. The animals, who once roamed free, had perished or fled to find new habitats. The people who lived nearby were struggling to survive, as they had lost their means of livelihood. The negative effects of climate change were now impossible to ignore, and the future looked bleak.
